    "where Z denotes the normalization term, θ is the diffusion model parameter, and ϕ is the classifier parameter.",
    "By taking the logarithm of both sides of the above equation and expanding it, we can obtain",
    "where g = ∇ xt log p ϕ (y|x t)| xt=µ.",
    "It can be seen that compared to the unconditional transition distribution, the conditional transition distribution also follows a Gaussian distribution, and the variance Σ is the same as the unconditional transition distribution p θ (x t |x t+1).",
    "At the same time, the mean has a shift of Σg, which also includes gradient information from the classifier."
